results.name: Product of all primes contained as binary substrings in binary representation of n.
example: n=7: product of the A078827(7)=3 primes as binary substrings in binary representation of 7 -> '111': a(7) = '11'*'11'*'111' = 3*3*7 = 63.
results.author: _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Dec 08 2002
